## Description {#details}

A container for analyses that lazily runs them and caches their results.

This class can manage analyses for any IR unit where the address of the IR unit sufficies as its identity.

Definition at line 253 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanager-h">PassManager.h</a>.

List of analysis pass IDs and associated concept pointers.

Requires iterators to be valid across appending new entries and arbitrary erases. Provides the analysis <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/callingconv/#abdf8cf606905c10634e831390981b0ed">ID</a> to enable finding iterators to a given entry in maps below, and provides the storage for the actual result concept.

## Public Member Functions

### clear() {#a4926331431f03253ee3ec8e6e3bb9d1c}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename IRUnitT, typename... ExtraArgTs&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>void llvm::AnalysisManager&lt; IRUnitT, ExtraArgTs &gt;::clear (IRUnitT &amp; IR, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">llvm::StringRef</a> Name)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Clear any cached analysis results for a single unit of IR.

This doesn&#39;t invalidate, but instead simply deletes, the relevant results. It is useful when the IR is being removed and we want to clear out all the memory pinned for it.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanager-h/#l00388">388</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanager-h">PassManager.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanagerimpl-h/#l00119">119</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanagerimpl-h">PassManagerImpl.h</a>.

### clear() {#a1def78d3ab800e1f9b15ac7f772862ff}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename IRUnitT, typename... ExtraArgTs&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>void llvm::AnalysisManager&lt; IRUnitT, ExtraArgTs &gt;::clear ()</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Clear all analysis results cached by this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/analysismanager">AnalysisManager</a>.

Like <code>clear(IRUnitT&amp;)</code>, this doesn&#39;t invalidate the results; it simply deletes them. This lets you clean up the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/analysismanager">AnalysisManager</a> when the set of IR units itself has potentially changed, and thus we can&#39;t even look up a a result and invalidate/clear it directly.

### getResult() {#aaab1fad63e4f3b8679469720a873fedd}

<MemberDefinition

  prototype={<>PassT::Result &amp; llvm::AnalysisManager&lt; IRUnitT, ExtraArgTs &gt;::getResult (IRUnitT &amp; IR, ExtraArgTs... ExtraArgs)</>}

### registerPass() {#a91ff894f756175a693c85bf73f79de9e}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;typename PassBuilderT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>bool llvm::AnalysisManager&lt; IRUnitT, ExtraArgTs &gt;::registerPass (PassBuilderT &amp;&amp; PassBuilder)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/register">Register</a> an analysis pass with the manager.

The parameter is a callable whose result is an analysis pass. This allows passing in a lambda to construct the analysis.

The analysis type to register is the type returned by calling the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder">PassBuilder</a></code> argument. If that type has already been registered, then the argument will not be called and this function will return false. Otherwise, we register the analysis returned by calling <code>PassBuilder()</code>, and this function returns true.

(Note: Although the return value of this function indicates whether or not an analysis was previously registered, you should just register all the analyses you might want and let this class run them lazily. This idiom lets us minimize the number of times we have to look up analyses in our hashtable.)

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanager-h/#l00471">471</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/passmanager-h">PassManager.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
